page.title: 01Stallingborough village
page.content: The village of{Stallingborough}is in the county of Humberside.It is 8 miles north west of{Grimsby}and 3 miles from Immingham.It is the coastal plain at the foot of the{Wolds}.The population is about 940 people and there are 315 houses.There is a main railway running through the village and the A1136 and the new A180 motorway link run to the south and north respectively. Stallingborough is surrounded by farmland with good soil for arable crops.Some of the crops grown are potatoes,peas,sprouts,wheat and barley.There are some pastures with cows and a few sheep. Stallingborough village is residential .There are a few jobs in the village or on the farms.Most people work at the{Humber {Bank}factories such as Norsk Hydro and Titans while other people work in Grimsby or Immingham.
